# Module 6: Unity Catalog

# Topic 52: Row-Level Security (RLS) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

## Why?

Suppose an employee in the **India** team logs in.

Should they see **USA** employee records?

❌ No.

They should only see **India** records.

This is where **Row-Level Security** comes in.

---

## Concept

**Row-Level Security (RLS)** restricts **which rows** a user can view.

> **Simple Definition:** Same table, different rows for different users.

---

## Theory

Employee Table

| ID | Name  | Country |
| -- | ----- | ------- |
| 1  | Alice | India   |
| 2  | Bob   | USA     |
| 3  | John  | UK      |

### India User

Sees

| ID | Name  | Country |
| -- | ----- | ------- |
| 1  | Alice | India   |

### USA User

Sees

| ID | Name | Country |
| -- | ---- | ------- |
| 2  | Bob  | USA     |

Same table.

Different rows.

---

## Architecture

```text id="v3ov3x"
Employee Table
        │
        ▼
 Row-Level Security
        │
   ┌────┴────┐
   ▼         ▼
India User  USA User
   │         │
India Rows  USA Rows
```

---

## Syntax

Implemented using **Row Filters** (or dynamic views, depending on the setup).

Concept is more important than syntax for interviews.

---

## Interview Questions

### What is Row-Level Security?

Restricts access to specific rows based on the user.

---

### Does RLS create multiple tables?

No.

One table.

Different users see different rows.

---

## Real-world Use

* Banking
* HR
* Healthcare
* Multi-country companies

---

## Common Mistake

❌ Thinking RLS hides columns.

---

# Topic 53: Column-Level Security (CLS) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

## Why?

Suppose HR has:

| Employee | Salary | PAN |
| -------- | ------ | --- |

Should every employee see Salary and PAN?

❌ No.

Only HR Managers should.

---

## Concept

**Column-Level Security (CLS)** restricts **which columns** a user can access.

> **Simple Definition:** Same table, different columns for different users.

---

## Theory

Employee Table

| ID | Name | Salary |
| -- | ---- | ------ |

### HR Manager

| ID | Name | Salary |
| -- | ---- | ------ |

### Employee

| ID | Name |
| -- | ---- |

Salary is hidden.

---

## Architecture

```text id="7lrd8o"
Employee Table
       │
       ▼
Column-Level Security
       │
  ┌────┴────┐
  ▼         ▼
 HR      Employee
All      Salary Hidden
```

---

## Syntax

Implemented using **Column Masks** (or views, depending on the setup).

Again, interviews focus more on the concept than the exact syntax.

---

## Interview Questions

### What is Column-Level Security?

Restricts access to specific columns.

---

### Difference between RLS and CLS?

RLS filters rows.

CLS hides columns.

---

## Real-world Use

* Salary
* Aadhaar
* PAN
* Credit Card
* Medical Records

---

## Common Mistake

❌ Thinking CLS removes rows.

---

# ⭐ Most Asked Interview Question

## Row-Level Security vs Column-Level Security

| Row-Level Security                    | Column-Level Security                |
| ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Controls rows                         | Controls columns                     |
| Filters records                       | Hides sensitive fields               |
| Same columns                          | Same rows                            |
| Different users see different records | Different users see different fields |

---

# 🏢 Real-World Example

Employee Table

| ID | Name  | Country | Salary |
| -- | ----- | ------- | ------ |
| 1  | Alice | India   | 80K    |
| 2  | Bob   | USA     | 100K   |
| 3  | John  | India   | 90K    |

### India Employee

| ID | Name  | Country |
| -- | ----- | ------- |
| 1  | Alice | India   |
| 3  | John  | India   |

* **RLS** → Only India rows.
* **CLS** → Salary column hidden.

